&lt;p&gt;Nuitée is at the forefront of a revolution—delivering AI-powered, smarter, and more personalized travel experiences for a new era.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Remote in EU or Dubai, or hybrid in Barcelona.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuitée is hiring a Commercial Operations Manager to work directly with our SVP of Sales &amp;amp; Partnerships and build the operating layer behind a fast-growing commercial team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll support the commercial team across proposals, RFPs, customer meetings, partner events, research, reporting, and follow-up, making sure important work is prepared, organised, and moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new role at Nuitée. Today, too much of this operational work sits with senior commercial leaders. Your job is to bring structure to it: preparing materials, coordinating inputs, tracking next steps, organising information, and making sure important commercial work keeps moving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good way to think of it is: you help build the practical operating layer behind a fast-growing commercial team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What makes it interesting for you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You work directly with our SVP of Sales &amp;amp; Partnerships and learn how senior commercial decisions are made&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You learn how major enterprise partnerships are built in practice: proposals, RFPs, meeting preparation, partner events, follow-up, and internal coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You support work around strategic relationships with large companies like Grab, Revolut, Citibank, and others&lt;/li&gt;
