&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re the face of a core product in the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You get a lot of agency to improve, change, and build, with little red tape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You work in a product-driven environment where things move quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a direct voice in technical and product decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recently raised a $48M Series A led by Accel. The company was already profitable before the round, and has grown 10x since 2022. You’ll receive a meaningful equity plan, so you join with both momentum and upside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role fits someone who:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;is very strong in Go&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;has balanced hands-on work with leadership, product, and stakeholder management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;has built and launched products at high-growth startups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;is comfortable in backend/API and infrastructure-heavy environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;has the judgment to make good calls in ambiguous situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;is a strong communicator who can represent the product and inspire others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;likes moving fast and taking initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuitée is fast-moving, low on process, and high on agency. That works very well for people who like momentum and ownership, and less so for people who prefer things to be neatly structured before they get going.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If that resonates, we’d love to hear from you. You can apply with your LinkedIn profile or CV. The application process is straightforward, and our hiring processes usually take 2 to 3 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Nuitee?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Nuitée, we are building the API backbone for the global travel industry. Founded in 2017, Nuitée is on a mission to transform a fragmented travel ecosystem with simple, scalable, and API-first infrastructure—think “Stripe for Travel.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By enabling seamless connectivity between hotels, OTAs, fintechs, super-apps, and businesses, some of which are entering the travel market for the first time, Nuitée empowers companies to deliver reliable travel products effortlessly. Our robust platform simplifies complex supplier networks, offering direct access to hotel inventory with better pricing, coverage, and technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With teams across the globe, including hubs in London, New York, San Francisco, Palma de Mallorca and Casablanca, Nuitée has grown into a global infrastructure provider trusted by industry leaders like Hopper, Priceline, Google, and Uber.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now backed by leading VCs and world-class investors including leaders from &lt;a href=&quot;http://booking.com/&quot;&gt;Booking.com&lt;/a&gt;, Stripe, and Shopify, Nuitée is positioned to redefine the B2B travel market, streamline operations for hotels, and enable new applications through cutting-edge APIs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuitée is at the forefront of a revolution—delivering AI-powered, smarter, and more personalized travel experiences for a new era.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Remote in EU or hybrid in Barcelona.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuitée is hiring a Supplier Connectivity &amp;amp; Onboarding Manager (Travel), to lead and scale our core supply operations functions: Onboarding, Loading, and Connectivity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead a team of around 15 people across these three functions, sitting at the centre of the supply organisation, accountable for making sure supply partners are onboarded efficiently, data quality is maintained, connectivity issues are resolved proactively, and operational performance keeps improving as Nuitée scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new role at Nuitée. As the supply team has grown to around 30 people across regions, the need for a dedicated operational leader has become clear. Your job is to bring clear structure: ownership, processes, SLAs, and reporting that the team can actually run on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good way to think of it: you build the operational backbone behind one of the company&#39;s biggest growth targets, and act as the connective tissue between the technical and commercial sides of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What makes it interesting for you&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You lead a team from day one: 15 people across Onboarding, Loading, and Connectivity, within a broader supply org of around 30&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There are no legacy processes to untangle. You design the SOPs, SLAs, and reporting frameworks from scratch and see your fingerprint on how the entire supply org operates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You sit at the intersection of Engineering, Product, Commercial, and Account Management, a rare vantage point to understand how the whole business actually works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hotel onboarding, inventory loading, and supplier connectivity are hard to get right at scale. You get to bring real structure and rigor to that problem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuitée has grown 10x since 2022, and was profitable already before raising a $48M Series A led by Accel. The supply organisation has real momentum and an aggressive growth target ahead of it, and this role is central to hitting it.&lt;/p&gt;
